description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and innovative dietitian with an interest in working in a forensic mental health and learning disability/autism service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides inpatient care to individuals with significant and complex mental health issues, personality disorders or learning disability and autism, and who may have come into conflict with the law because of this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is part of a pilot project focusing on physical health and weight management in our population, and we would be keen to hear form anyone interested in such a project, even if they dont have significant amounts of experience in a similar setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant would feel passionate about the contribution a dietician could make to the health and wellbeing of patients with complex psychological needs, would thrive working in a varied and multidisciplinary setting (including colleagues from a medical, nursing, psychology, OT, SALT, social work, and sports therapy background) - and would also be comfortable working autonomously. The successful applicant would also have excellent clinical and communication skills, and demonstrate an ability to be flexible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pilot is fixed term 12 months in the first instance. The post would be available as a secondment to anyone already working in the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDavid VON BRANDTEmail addressd.vonbrandt@nhs.netTelephone number02085102130Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David VON BRANDT, telephone 02085102130, email d.vonbrandt@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
